modules.description: This module implements HTTP client operations using cURL with Lwt for asynchronous execution. It supports making GET, POST, PUT, DELETE, and other HTTP requests with customizable headers, request bodies, and retry logic. The module works with URLs, HTTP methods, and cURL options, returning structured responses that include status codes, headers, body content, and metadata like response time and redirect count. Concrete use cases include interacting with REST APIs, downloading or uploading data, and handling redirects and authentication challenges programmatically.
